cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper proposes an iterative auction mechanism to compute optimal charging schedules while considering the strategic behavior of self-interested agents. The game theoretical analysis of the proposed auction also supports this category.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a mechanism to elicit users' preferences and compute optimal schedules, which involves AI techniques such as preference elicitation and optimization.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an iterative auction mechanism that computes high-quality schedules, which can be seen as a learning process to improve the efficiency of the auction.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper considers a scheduling problem in the context of electric vehicle charging stations, which involves control and optimization of the charging process.
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper considers the social welfare of all users and the privacy preservation of individual users in the charging scheduling problem, which relates to the societal impact of computing.
